http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Tue 28 Dec 2021
Source: OIE-WAHIS (World Animal Health Information System) 2021 [edited]
https://wahis.oie.int/#/report-info?reportId=45405


Rift Valley fever virus (infection with), Niger
-----------------------------------------
General information
Report type: immediate notification
Started: 22 Nov 2021
Confirmed: 30 Nov 2021
Reported: 28 Dec 2021
Reason for notification: recurrence
Last occurrence: 30 Mar 2017
Causal agent: Rift Valley fever virus
Nature of diagnosis: clinical, laboratory
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country.

Outbreak location: Commune of Tassara, ZR Tchin-Tabaraden, Tchin-Tabarade, Tahoua
Started: 22 Nov 2021
Ended: 24 Dec 2021
Epidemiological unit: village
Affected animals
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Killed and disposed of / Slaughtered or killed for commercial use / Vaccinated
Goats / 350 / 111 / 46 / 0 / 0 / 0

Affected population: abortion, orchitis, retained placenta and mortalities in a small ruminant herd.

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: unknown or inconclusive

Control measures at event level
Domestic control measures applied: screening, surveillance within containment and/or protection zone, vector surveillance, zoning

Wild control measures applied: vector surveillance

Diagnostic test results: not available

[The location of the outbreak can be seen on the interactive map included in the OIE report at the source URL above.]

--
communicated by:
ProMED

[According to the OIE WAHIS database, Rift Valley fever (animals) was last reported in Nigeria in March 2017. This event started in September 2016; the final follow-up report is available at https://wahis.oie.int/#/report-info?reportId=24701. According to this last report, the event was resolved. This event affected humans and animals.

"Between 2 Aug and 9 Oct 2016, Niger reported 101 human cases of suspected RVF, including 28 deaths. All RVF cases were in Tchintabaraden and Abalak health districts in the Tahoua region."

"One RVF outbreak affecting cattle and small ruminants in Tansala village in Tahoua region, was officially reported to the World Organisation for Animal Health (OIE) on 19 Sep 2016."
(https://www.fao.org/3/i7055e/i7055e.pdf)

No human cases linked to this current outbreak have been reported. - Mod.CRD

HealthMap/ProMED map of Tahoua Region, Niger: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=8700579,32064.]
